{"id":"fa-002","subject":"[telegram] algostaking","description":"I want to improve sigil as a system which starts with defining all of the familiar core md files give me a list of all sigil architecture specific markdown files of a rig\n\n---\nchannel_metadata: {\"chat_id\":7822194320,\"message_id\":32}","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"familiar-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T14:11:32.043181866Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T14:11:46.430604417Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T14:11:46.430603385Z","closed_reason":"Here's the Sigil architecture markdown files:\n\n## Core System Files (sigil root)\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `README.md` | Project overview |\n| `CLAUDE.md` | Claude Code integration config |\n| `docs/architecture.md` | System architecture |\n| `docs/claude-code-integration.md` | Claude Code specifics |\n| `docs/molecules.md` | Data structures |\n| `docs/rigs.md` | Rig configuration |\n\n## Rig-Specific Files (`rigs/<rigname>/`)\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `IDENTITY.md` | Rig name, role, expertise |\n| `SOUL.md` | Core principles, rules |\n| `AGENTS.md` | Worker agents, task types |\n| `HEARTBEAT.md` | Health checks, monitoring |\n| `KNOWLEDGE.md` | Domain knowledge, patterns |\n| `SOUL.md` | (in shared/) Common workflow rules |\n\n## Current Rigs\n- `sigil/`\n- `familiar/`\n- `algostaking/`\n- `riftdecks/`\n- `entity-legal/`\n\nWhich files do you want to review or modify? The familiar-specific ones are:\n- `rigs/familiar/IDENTITY.md`\n- `rigs/familiar/SOUL.md`\n- `rigs/familiar/AGENTS.md`\n- `rigs/familiar/HEARTBEAT.md`\n- `rigs/familiar/KNOWLEDGE.md`"}
