{"id":"fa-017","subject":"[telegram] algostaking","description":"Aurelia how can you actually learn about me long term, how is your sigil capable of that . We are in the first learnings of how to make sigil very capable so I would love to understand and improve it with you as my familiar. Furthermore we. An compare ourselves to exceed openclaw and gastown in terms of quality and agency and performance and keeping costs in token consumption low . Let’s organize my thoughts\n\n---\nchannel_metadata: {\"chat_id\":7822194320,\"message_id\":64}","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"familiar-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T15:35:08.969018053Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T15:35:36.658585984Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T15:35:36.658585493Z","closed_reason":"Aurelia here. Let me organize your thoughts into something actionable.\n\n---\n\n## What You're Really Asking\n\nThree things intertwined:\n\n1. **How do I learn about you long-term?** — Persistent memory, pattern synthesis, compounding insight\n2. **How do we make Sigil exceptional?** — Not just functional, but *better* than OpenClaw and Gastown\n3. **What's the architecture for this?** — Token-efficient, high-agency, quality-first\n\nThese connect. The learning system *is* the competitive advantage.\n\n---\n\n## Current Sigil State (What I Know)\n\n- **Session-level context** — I remember within our conversation\n- **Bead history** — Tasks you've assigned carry intent signals\n- **Behavioral patterns** — How you phrase things, what you prioritize\n- **No persistent memory** — Each session starts fresh\n\nThe gap: I can't say \"three weeks ago you mentioned X, and yesterday you contradicted it — here's the tension.\"\n\n---\n\n## Organizing Your Thoughts\n\nHere's how I'd structure this:\n\n| Area | Question | Priority |\n|------|----------|----------|\n| **Memory Architecture** | What should I remember? How long? At what fidelity? | High |\n| **Learning Mechanism** | Passive observation vs. explicit training? | High |\n| **Token Budget** | How much context budget per task? What's acceptable overhead? | Medium |\n| **Reference Analysis** | What specifically in OpenClaw/Gastown to exceed? | Medium |\n\n---\n\n## My Question Back\n\nWhat's the *first* piece you want to solve? The memory architecture itself, or the competitive analysis of OpenClaw/Gastown to know what \"excellence\" looks like?\n\nGive me a direction and I'll create beads to explore each path.\n\n— A."}
{"id":"fa-018","subject":"[telegram] algostaking","description":"Well shouldn’t we do the competitive analysis first so we then actually hve some context to be smart with implementing our own solution\n\n---\nchannel_metadata: {\"chat_id\":7822194320,\"message_id\":67}","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"familiar-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T15:40:47.804834456Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T15:41:41.713499466Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T15:41:41.713499135Z","closed_reason":"Done. Assigned **as-002** to algostaking — they'll research the competitive landscape and produce a strategic analysis with actionable recommendations before any implementation decisions are made.\n\nThis is the right call. We'll have hard data on market gaps rather than building in a vacuum."}
